[~blbradley] I just checked the stack overflow link you posted . The error user reported is because they are running the WordCountTopology in LocalCluster and in LocalCluster   we run it for 10 seconds before we call       cluster.shutdown(); which throws the InterrupttedException  . So its not an issue you can test it by running in a single node cluster.
cluster.submitTopology("word-count", conf, builder.createTopology());
Thread.sleep(10000);
